<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1901-07-03T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1901-07-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="427" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d427">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Sickles</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Madrid</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1901-07-03"><hi rend="italic">July 3,
                                1901</hi>.</date></dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 512.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the
                            receipt to-day of your telegraphic instruction in reply to my cablegram
                            of the 30th instant.</p>
                        <p>The purport of your cablegram has been repeated at once by wire to the
                            consul-general at Barcelona.</p>
                        <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Stanton Sickles</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Chargé d’Affaires ad
                            interim.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>